    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_293054669" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/293054669" />
    <a title="Kelly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1347210-kelly"><img alt="Kelly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1310833806p2/1347210.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/293054669?book_show_action=true">Mar 12, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelly" href="/user/show/1347210-kelly">Kelly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780316058599" href="/book/show/595415.The_Ice_Queen">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1347210-kelly?shelf=cutting_for_pleasure">cutting_for_pleasure</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1347210-kelly?shelf=love">love</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1347210-kelly?shelf=cried-like-a-baby">cried-like-a-baby</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1347210-kelly?shelf=lit">lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1347210-kelly?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1347210-kelly?shelf=depressing">depressing</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1347210-kelly?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1347210-kelly?shelf=romance">romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer293054669&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer293054669" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13909169114654925835">Rather than write yet another review detailing my love/hate relationship with Ms. Hoffman, opine on her writing style, and gush about how expertly she crafted the impact of <i>the after</i>, I&apos;m going to instead share one line/moment that stuck with me from each chapter. And just to keep things interesting and convey information about the book while still being lazy, I’ve created my own soundtrack for it. But be warned, as this was not a very happy book, neither are the songs that accompany it.<br/><br/><a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sb_G1Ov0q6Q&amp;list=PL6D13255BD97197D3&amp;index=12' rel='nofollow noopener'>&quot;The mom</a></span>
  <span id="freeText13909169114654925835" style="display:none">Rather than write yet another review detailing my love/hate relationship with Ms. Hoffman, opine on her writing style, and gush about how expertly she crafted the impact of <i>the after</i>, I'm going to instead share one line/moment that stuck with me from each chapter. And just to keep things interesting and convey information about the book while still being lazy, I’ve created my own soundtrack for it. But be warned, as this was not a very happy book, neither are the songs that accompany it.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sb_G1Ov0q6Q&amp;list=PL6D13255BD97197D3&amp;index=12" rel="nofollow noopener">"The moment that changes the path of a life is one that's invisible, that dissolves like sugar in water."</a><br /><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vt1Pwfnh5pc" rel="nofollow noopener">“Do you think every person has one defining secret? The essence of a person. The secret that if you figure it out, you figure out the riddle of that particular human being. “<br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PYzCXx7Ndok" rel="nofollow noopener">“All I could hear was the sound of the tap. I understood that it was the only way we could be together – the elements most drawn to each other are the ones that destroy each other.”<br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p9krDpXAPS4" rel="nofollow noopener">“We were moving into the <i>after</i>; the <i>then</i> and the <i>now</i> and the <i>soon will be</i> were becoming separate realms. This had been happiness and we didn’t know it. We walked right past. Had no idea. Step after step. “<br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CVc91Ia5wqU" rel="nofollow noopener">“Memory that is stronger than the present, that stays imprinted behind your eyes, layering itself over everything you see in the present, in the here and now.”<br /></a><br /><br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u9sq3ME0JHQ" rel="nofollow noopener">“It was the time I would remember, more than the fish, tub, ice, pond, fast, hard, slow, baby; it was this, drowning while I knew he was thinking about leaving. We were a human example of chaos theory, thrown together by circumstance. We didn’t belong together, I knew that. But for one night we were perfect.”<br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DXHB_wgXsw4" rel="nofollow noopener">“I loved him in a way that was over. A way that was the beginning of something. The sort of love that opened you up for more.” <br /></a><br /><br /> <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZH2WpV3Pl24&amp;list=PLM6OOVHRyfiC5HSnzNz62VJDC2ZzTFVwP&amp;index=14" rel="nofollow noopener">“Magic was real – if the tiniest of actions reverberated throughout the universe in invisible and unexpected ways, changing the weather and the climate, then anything was possible”</a><br /> <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13909169114654925835" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


